Knowledge Integration Module Integrates data in an Microsoft SQL Server target table in incremental update mode. Inexistent rows are inserted; already existing rows are updated. Data can be controlled. Erroneous data is isolated in the error table and can be recycled.
When using this module with a journalized source table, it is possible to synchronize deletions.
Restrictions: - Comparison of data is made using the Update Key defined in the interface. It has to be set. - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - The FLOW_CONTROL option calls the Knowledge Control Module to isolate the errors. If not set, an error occurs. - Deletes are commited regardless of the COMMIT option
Check this option if you want to create the target table
Check this option if you want to truncate the target table.
Check this option if you want to delete all rows
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface
Uncheck this option if you do not want to insert new data in the target table
Uncheck this option if you do not want to update existing data in the target table
Uncheck this option if you do not want to perform a flow control
Check this option to recycle previous errors
Check this option to control the target table after the insert operation
Uncheck this option to not commit your update or/and insert operations on your target table. This option is set to true by default.
create table <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "\t[COL_NAME]\t[DEST_CRE_DT] NULL", ",\n", "", "INS OR UPD")%>, IND_UPDATE char(1) )

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> (<%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "(INS OR UPD) AND NOT TRG")%>, IND_UPDATE) select <%=snpRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=snpRef.getColList("", "\t[EXPRESSION]", ",\n", "", "(INS OR UPD) AND NOT TRG")%>, <% if (snpRef.getPop("HAS_JRN").equals("0")) { %> 'I' IND_UPDATE <%} else {%> JRN_FLAG <%}%> from <%=snpRef.getFrom()%> where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJoin()%> <%=snpRef.getFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=snpRef.getHaving()%>

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> (<%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "(INS OR UPD) AND NOT TRG")%>, IND_UPDATE) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "(INS OR UPD) AND NOT TRG ")%>, 'I' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> E where not exists (select '?' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("", "\t\tT.[COL_NAME]=E.[COL_NAME]", "\nand", "", "(UK)")%> ) and E.ORIGIN='<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ERR_TYPE='<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'

delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> where exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> I where <%=snpRef.getColList("", snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A") + ".[COL_NAME] = I.[COL_NAME]", "\n\tand \t", "", "(UK)")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'D' )
Remove deleted rows from flow table
Create Unique Index on flow table

update S set IND_UPDATE = 'U' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")%> S, <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where (<%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]=S.[COL_NAME]", " and ", "", "UK")%>)

Update S set IND_UPDATE = 'N' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")%> S, <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where (<%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]=S.[COL_NAME]", " and ", "", "UK")%>) and (<%=snpRef.getColList("","((T.[COL_NAME]=S.[COL_NAME]) Or (T.[COL_NAME] IS NULL and S.[COL_NAME] IS NULL))", " \nand\t", "", "(UPD AND (NOT TRG)) AND (NOT UK) ")%>)

Update T set T.DF_VAL=S.DD_VAL from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")%> S, <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where (<%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]=S.[COL_NAME]", " and ", "", "UK") %>) and S.IND_UPDATE = 'U'

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> (<%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "INS AND (NOT TRG)")%><%=snpRef.getColList(",","[COL_NAME]", " , " , "", "INS AND TRG")%>) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "\t[COL_NAME]", ",\n", "", "INS AND (NOT TRG)")%><%=snpRef.getColList(",","[EXPRESSION]", " , " , "", "INS AND TRG")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> where IND_UPDATE = 'I' OR IND_UPDATE = 'U'

update T set T.DF_VAL=getdate(), T.ID_TRT_ALI=<%=snpRef.getSession("SESS_NO")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> T WHERE DF_VAL='01/01/9999' and not exists ( select * from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> S where <%=snpRef.getColList("", "S.[COL_NAME]=T.[COL_NAME]", "\n\tand\t", "", "PK=1")%>)
